uk.ac.gate.cloud.data

Class DataBundle

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.gate.cloud.common.ApiObject
      • uk.ac.gate.cloud.data.DataBundleSummary
        • uk.ac.gate.cloud.data.DataBundle

  • public class DataBundle
extends DataBundleSummary
    Full details of a data bundle, and methods to configure and download the bundle contents. Note that while many of the fields on this object are public, direct modifications to the field values will not be reflected in the server-side state - use the manipulation methods to modify the details on the server.
    Author:
    Ian Roberts

    • Field Detail

      • dateCreated

        public String dateCreated
        Date that this bundle was initially created.

      • totalSize

        public long totalSize
        The total size of this bundle, in bytes, or 0 if the size is not known.

      • monthlyPrice

        public double monthlyPrice
        The price charged per month for storage of this bundle's data (may be zero).

      • type

        public InputType type
        The type of this input (ZIP, TAR, ARC, WARC, TWITTER_STREAM or DATASIFT_STREAM). May be null if this bundle is not suitable for use as input to an annotation job.

      • encoding

        public String encoding
        Character encoding to use when reading entries from the archives in this bundle. If null, the (W)ARC entry headers will be used to guess an appropriate encoding for each entry (in the case of ARC or WARC files) or a default of UTF-8 will be used (for other formats).

      • mimeTypeOverride

        public String mimeTypeOverride
        MIME type to use when parsing entries from the archive. If null the appropriate type will be guessed based on the file name extension and (in the case of (W)ARC files) the HTTP headers from the (W)ARC entry.

      • fileExtensions

        public String fileExtensions
        Comma-separated list of file extensions that will be processed. Entries that do not match any of these extensions will be ignored. If null all entries that represent files (as opposed to directories) will be processed. Should be left as null for Twitter input types, and will always be null for ARC inputs.

      • mimeTypeFilters

        public String mimeTypeFilters
        Space-separated list of MIME types used to filter the entries of interest from ARC and WARC input files. Entries whose MIME type does not match any of these will be ignored. Will be null for non-(W)ARC inputs.

      • files

        public List<Downloadable> files
        Files in this bundle. Call urlToDownload on each entry to get a (time-limited) URL from which the file can be downloaded.

      • addFile

        public void addFile(File inputFile)
        Upload a file to an open bundle.
        Parameters:
        inputFile - the file to upload. The last component of the File's path will be used as the name of the file in the bundle.

      • addFile

        public void addFile(String fileName,
           int contentLength,
           InputStream source)
        Upload a file to an open bundle.
        Parameters:
        fileName - the name to use for the bundle entry
        contentLength - the number of bytes to upload
        source - an input stream from which the file's content can be read. It must provide exactly contentLength bytes up to end-of-file. The stream will be read to EOF but will not be closed by this method, the caller is responsible for ensuring the stream is properly closed.

      • close

        public void close()
        Close a bundle that is open for uploads.

      • delete

        public void delete()
        Delete this bundle, which also deletes any contained files that are stored in the default GATE Cloud-managed location.
